<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="620" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[786,1379,1870,2294]" pageId="22" pageNumber="620">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[790,1045,1989,2018]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="620" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inclusus">Gerbilliscus inclusus</taxonomicName>
has generally been con- sidered a representative of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1231,1318,2024,2058]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="620" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="afer">G. afer</taxonomicName>
species group. The species, however, has not yet been sequenced and its affinities are not known. Three subspecies have been recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
